President Obama has declared a major disaster in Rhode Island due to the impact of Tropical Storm Irene. This declaration allows for federal aid to supplement state and local recovery efforts. The funding will be available for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures. Gracia B. Szczech has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected area. Further assessments are ongoing, and additional forms of assistance may be designated in the future. For more information, contact the FEMA News Desk.